This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with face age progression, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the presence of variations in pose, expression, and makeup, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a pyramidal adversarial discriminator suggests that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
